
-------Greek Burger Recipe ------

1) In a small bowl, mix together mayonnaise and minced garlic. Cover, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
2) Preheat grill for high heat.
3) Mix together lamb, breadcrumbs, fennel, shallot, oregano, and salt. Form into 3/4-inch-thick patties, 
   and sprinkle black pepper over each.
4) Brush grate with olive oil, and place burgers on grill. Cook for 3 to 5 minutes per side, turning once,
   or until done. Serve on buns with garlic mayonnaise.
